Three Monkeys booking parity with Baboon + origin tracking + redesign

Admin /bookings list (parity with Baboon Phuket):
- Compact column layout: Ref · Booked · Customer · Reservation · Time ·
  Guests · Zone/Table · Add-ons · Deposit · Notes · Origin · Status
- New "Zone / Table" column (3M-specific) shows zone name with table_code
  badge (MD2, BP1, etc.) from the allotment system
- New "Add-ons" column shows each promotional add-on with quantity
- New "Notes" column shows special_requests with overflow tooltip
- New "Origin" column shows booking + payment country flags via
  react-country-flag (Globe = booking IP country, CreditCard = card country)
- Hotel name visible inline under Zone/Table when transport=hotel_pickup
- Customer column shows country code + phone, kept Baboon's two-line look
- Search now also matches table_code and zone name

Origin tracking (mirrors Baboon's data shape so OneBooking sees identical
payloads from every source site):
- Migration 011: adds booking_origin_ip, booking_origin_country_code/name +
  payment_origin_country_code/name columns to bookings
- lib/geo/ip-lookup.ts: ip-api.com lookup with 3s timeout + getClientIP
  helper (Vercel/Cloudflare/standard proxy header chain) + ISO country
  name map
- create-payment-intent captures client IP and geolocates BEFORE inserting
  the booking row so the data is on the row from the start
- Stripe webhook fetches payment_method.card.country on
  payment_intent.succeeded and stores it in payment_origin_country_code/name

OneBooking sync payload extended:
- New BookingOrigin + PaymentOrigin types
- BookingSyncPayload now carries booking_origin and payment_origin objects
- pushBookingToOneBooking accepts both and forwards them so the OneBooking
  dashboard can display country flags for every Three Monkeys booking just
  like it does for Baboon

Checkout success page redesign:
- Now uses /images/threemonkeyslogo.png at the top
- Brand-matching background (black + soft olive glow, subtle dot grid)
- New copy: "Reservation Confirmed · Your table awaits"
- Shows the assigned dining zone ("Seated in Monkey Dome") if available
- Map card is now clickable (opens Google Maps to Three Monkeys)
- Cleaned phone number in footer

Booking confirmation email:
- Logo path swapped to /images/threemonkeyslogo.png
- New "Authentic Southern Thai · Phuket" tagline under logo in olive on
  black to reinforce branding
